# {{ project }}

This is a Javelin workspace application.

## What lives here

- Application code and routes
- Workspace-specific Maven dependencies
- App config in `config/`
- Generated and runtime files under `storage/`

## Bootstrap

From this directory:

```bash
./install.sh
```

On Windows:

```powershell
.\install.ps1
```

The installer checks Java and Maven, then runs `mvn test` inside the workspace.

## Framework dependency

This workspace consumes Javelin through Maven:

```xml
<dependency>
    <groupId>io.javelin</groupId>
    <artifactId>javelin-starter</artifactId>
    <version>${javelin.version}</version>
</dependency>
```

Add any other application libraries you need in this POM. The workspace is a normal Maven project.

## Developer commands

- `javelin serve`
- `javelin build`
- `javelin routes:list`
- `javelin make:controller UserController`

